> Thanks for reaching out. The `stable` images consume stable RPMs from Fedora, and per https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/?packages=skopeo there hasn’t been an update to 1.22 in the Fedora 43 release.

@mtrmac The F43 update for skopeo 1.22 is at https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2026-c623038804 (In the link you mentioned, it's seen as one of two updates in `testing`, with title `buildah-1.43.0-1.fc43, containers-common-0.67.0-1.fc43, & 2 more `

> [@lsm5](https://github.com/lsm5) are we now frozen in F43? I do see the updates for F44+F45.

The F43 bodhi has +3 karma but I've disabled auto-stable for it because it also contains `podman v5.8.0` which has the `boltdb -> sqlite migration feature`, with a [test week](https://fedoramagazine.org/podman-test-days-try-the-new-backend-parallel-pulls/) starting tomorrow until Friday next week. So, I hope to move it to stable next week

@foster-hangdaan would you be ok with running updating the skopeo package using updates-testing repo in the existing image ?
